Module Common
Package dk.sdu.cbse.common.services

Interface IPostProcess

public interface IPostProcess
Interface for processing a plugin after the main game processes for that specific time frame have been executed.

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type
    Method
    Description
    void
    process(GameData gameData, World world)
    This method runs once every frame, however, after the primary processes have executed, so entities and their states can be evaluated (For instance collision)
    Preconditions The method IProcess.process(GameData, World) runs prior to this method, as well as the method IPlugin.start(GameData, World)
    Postconditions - Entity states may have been updated based on post calculations, such as collisions, health deducted etc.

  • Method Details

    • process

      void process(GameData gameData, World world)
      This method runs once every frame, however, after the primary processes have executed, so entities and their states can be evaluated (For instance collision)
      Preconditions
      • The method IProcess.process(GameData, World) runs prior to this method, as well as the method IPlugin.start(GameData, World)
      Postconditions
      • - Entity states may have been updated based on post calculations, such as collisions, health deducted etc.
      • - The world reflects the final state changes for this current frame.
      Parameters:
      gameData - Global instance of GameData class. Must not be null
      world - Global instance of World class. Must not be null
